:INFO
The Book That Required the Right Moment
Some books find you exactly when you need them. The Four Agreements was not that \
for me at first. I bought it at an airport bookshop, read 40 pages on the plane, \
and forgot about it. The second attempt ended at the same chapter. The third \
time I picked it up during a particularly difficult week at work and something \
about the agreement to not take anything personally hit me in a way it simply \
had not before. I finished it in two evenings.

